🔹   Main Categories of Map Methods

       1️.   Insertion Methods

        Used to add data into the map

         put(K key, V value) → add/update value
         putAll(Map m) → copy all entries
         
         
         map.put("A", 10);
         
         
       2️.  Retrieval Methods

           Used to get values

          get(Object key) → returns value
          getOrDefault(key, defaultValue)
          
          map.get("A");  // 10
          
          
          
       3. Removal Methods

           Used to delete data

           remove(Object key)
           remove(key, value)
          
           map.remove("A");
           
           
        4️. Checking Methods

        Used to check presence

           containsKey(key)
           containsValue(value)
           isEmpty()
           
           map.containsKey("A");
           
       
        5️.  Size / Utility Methods
              size()
              clear()   
              
        6. Traversal Methods (Very Important ⭐)

             Used to iterate map

             keySet() → returns all keys
             values() → returns all values
              entrySet() → key + value pair (most used in interview)     
              
              for (Map.Entry<String, Integer> entry : map.entrySet()) {
             System.out.println(entry.getKey() + " " + entry.getValue());
